As long as I can remember I’ve been drawn to grit & grime.
Urban decay, the dirt around the edges…

Back in 2004, Melrose Blvd was where it was at. The trendiest shops, the coolest kids, long before the Fairfax District, before Streetwear as we know it, before brands like The Hundreds changed the landscape.

But I wasn’t drawn to the storefronts. It was the back alleys behind the shops that pulled me in, with the taggers, the storytellers, the statement makers.
